<br>
I think the reason why you had a hard time jefm is because you tried to make it an actual sentence.  Grammatically speaking, in both English and Japanese &quot;Grits and Gravy&quot; is a fragment.  Therefore, you didn't need to go to all the trouble of trying to construct a full length sentence, in fact by doing so you made a lot of trouble for yourself.  'Wa' marks the subject of a sentece - grits is definately not the subject.  'Desu' is also not needed because you aren't saying &quot;this is grits and gravy&quot;.  'Mo' doesn't work either, in this case 'to' is used for &quot;and&quot;, mo is usually &quot;also&quot; or &quot;as well&quot;.<br>
<br>
I think all you need is: guritsu to gureibi.  Don't make things harder than they have to be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/3/02 7:25:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grits and Gravy</span><hr size=1> Yeah...I figured there was a better way...<br>
